<main>
<div id="mount"></div>
So, St Paul’s was built by Sir Christopher Wren in the 17th Century, in the English Baroque style. It was built as part of a major regeneration project in the City after the Great Fire of London. Obviously, that fire was nothing compared to the size of the wildfires they get over in Australia or California, or even France or Spain or Portugal nowadays — but for the time, it was a pretty big deal! Fires aren’t quite as big a thing in the UK at the moment — what do you think the main problem we have is?
 

