:: FG-13 {"position":"450,950","size":"100,100"}
<<set $passage to "FG-12B">><<set $nextpassage to "FG-14">><<set $map1 = setup.generateDirectionsMap([51.51235903720836, -0.09826818656430915],[51.51077966722368, -0.09844273228171523])>><<audio ":all" stop>><<audio "FG_13" play>>
<main>
<div id="mount"></div>
You see, when we have days and days of scaldingly hot weather, which have become really common in the summer, the ground can become particularly hard. What kind of summers are you guys getting in 2022? You had a 40 degree day? Pfft. Try a month of that. And add to that the way our cities are built here — tightly packed roads made out of concrete and stone — and it means that when rain does eventually fall hard and fast, the ground doesn’t let the water absorb, leading to these big floods which come on very very quickly, not leaving much time for people to prepare! Many, many homes are affected by this in London and elsewhere in the UK — almost five million. What we really need are homes that are built to withstand — oh, sorry. I’m getting off-topic. Dad warned me about this. Apparently I’ve got a tendency to meander. Right, let’s row down towards the Thames. We’ll row down St Peter’s Hill, towards Millennium Bridge, and pause at the river’s edge — where the river was in 2022, anyway.

$map1

<<button "We are at the river">><<set $prevpass to $passage>><<goto "FG-14">><</button>>

