Oh shoot. I told you I’m still a bit of a novice. I’ve forgotten to do the safety spiel. Dad’s going to kill me! I’ll just do it quickly now, if that’s okay with you guys.

Errr... Hello, everybody. My name is Kelly. On behalf of Waterworks Tours, I’d like to welcome you to the City of London. We do hope you will enjoy your stay. First off, drinking alcoholic beverages is NOT ALLOWED while on the gondola. We once had a terrible situation involving a bottle of sambuca and a stag do, and my dad — er, I mean, my boss — would like me to emphasise that Waterworks Tours’s insurance policy does NOT cover alcohol-based accidents. Got it?

Good.

Secondly, while in the gondola, please do keep your arms and legs inside the boat at all times. You do not want to be paddling around in the Thames, let me tell you. You can get an awful infection that way. And you may not mind, but I personally do not want to be getting my hair wet today, and I’ll be the one jumping in to save you if you do go overboard. So for the sake of my good hair day, please do keep all limbs inside the gondola. 

Finally, take precautions while in the sun. It is an unseasonably warm October day today in 2039, and we are going through a bit of heatwave, with the temperature going up to 27 degrees celsius. Nothing really to worry about — heatwaves in the autumn are pretty normal nowadays — but the UV rays from the sun can be very dangerous, so we do ask that you wear appropriate sunscreen and hats if needed. Last year on Christmas day, it was 13 degrees! Guess that’s just the world we live in, hey?

