Not as many people work or live here in the City anymore...as you might be able to tell. Pretty quiet, isn’t it? After the Coronavirus pandemic of 2020 — have you guys heard of that one? Apparently it was a pretty big deal — people who would usually come into the office in the City ended up working from home a lot more. Remote working, they called it. Slowly, a lot of these huge skyscrapers you can see got turned into different things — some of them got turned into huge greenhouses to tackle food shortages, which was pretty cool. And some of them got turned into social housing — which is great, but they are near flooding areas, and they’re all packed into their skyscrapers tight, like sardines. When the Thames Barrier went, so did a bunch of people, out of London. To be honest, rich people ended up moving further out of the City — more towards the North of England, actually, where they can be higher above the sea level. They left the cities and the poorest amongst them behind, on those new flood plains. 

