In 2022, there are a lot of cars in the City, right? Not today, but most days. A bunch of European cities actually ended up going car-free in their city centres in the late 2020s, but London never ended up getting to that stage...The thing about going car-free in what are usually the busiest places in the city is that it helps you notice things that you might not normally notice. People slow down a little, take their time, explore areas that usually get blocked off. The city ends up feeling bigger, better, more beautiful. And you really feel like you can breathe more, because air pollution goes down. I wonder if there’s something you guys could do about that. Emailing an MP? Going on climate protests? Cycling instead of using cars? I don’t mean to put the onus totally on you guys. If we really want to change the world for the better and avoid disaster, it has to be a mix of institutional change and individual change. Banning private planes might be a good start. Taxing big businesses properly. Hmm. What else? Can you think of any other ideas? Maybe three things you can do personally, and three things our governments can do? Give it a ponder for the rest of the tour.

